On August 12, 2009, President Obama delivered remarks at a reception honoring Justice Sonia Sotomayor. The audience included members of Sotomayor's family and friends, leaders of the Hispanic community, members of Congress, Supreme Court justices, judges from federal Courts of Appeals, members of law enforcement and advocacy groups, and administration officials. Expected attendees included First Lady Michelle Obama, members of the US Supreme Court, administration officials, members of Congress, federal Court of Appeals judges, and other elected officials and leaders.